<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-11T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-11T19:00:00-05:00" n="244" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d244">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 E.W. 1939/9–1044:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-11T20:00:00-04:00">September 11, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2185. Reurtel 3417 September 10. The Department has just now received
                                from the Joint Chiefs of Staff clearance on the protocol to
                                accompany the Rumanian armistice. Accordingly you are authorized to
                                sign the protocol, on behalf of this Government, or to agree to its
                                signature by a Soviet general.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>